{"word":"Ἰάς","slug":"Ἰάς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>Ἰάς</b></el> <el>(Ἰάς, άδος,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a> <a href='S:feminine'>fem.</a> of <el>Ἰάων, Ἴων</el>,\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>Ionian, Ionic</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>as <a href='S:Substantive'>Subst.</a> (<a href='S:subaudi, subaudito'>sub.</a> <el>γυνή</el>), <i>an Ionian woman</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>(<a href='S:subaudi, subaudito'>sub.</a> <el>γλῶσσα</el>) <i>the Ionic dialect</i>, <b><a href='S:Lucian'>Luc.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}